div.div: The end user will see a standard html page with select or text input boxes acting as
autoComplete. When the user selects or clicks on auto complete element.
This triggers javascript calls that then trigger a websocket message to the backend.
Websocket listener on front end is listening fo results due for any of the div ids available.
The moment they choose the next select auto complete box will have relevant data sent
via websockets for them to be able to then select next object
